The paper deals with natural language processing (NLP) and specifically focuses on the task of natural language to SQL (NL2SQL) conversion. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also involves working with a dataset (WikiSQL) and designing a model, which could fall under cs.DB (Databases) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) respectively. The use of BERT, a popular language model, could also suggest cs.LG (Learning) as a possible category. Finally, the paper involves analyzing the dataset and model performance, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
